profile_positions.description:
- Responsible for the 8th World Water Forum’s Judges and Prosecutors segment;
- Supported the drafting of the Brasilia Declaration of Judges on Water Justice; and
- Organized the 1st Conference of Judges and Prosecutors on Water Justice.

- Drafted judicial sentences for Justice Antonio Herman Benjamin;
- Conducted legal research on electoral and environmental law;
- Organized several high-level meetings on International Environmental Law, in partnership with IUCN's World Environmental Law Commission, UNEP and OAS; and
- Organized the Regional Judicial Colloquium for Latin America and the Caribbean.

- Responsible for international environmental affairs on Justice Antonio Herman Benjamin's Chambers;
- Drafted technical notes on Brazilian Environmental Law in Portuguese, English and Spanish, for recipients such as France’s Conseil d’État, International Organizations and Embassies;
- Facilitated the implementation of the Global Judicial Institute for the Environment; and
- Organized the 1st IUCN World Environmental Law Conference and the Inter-American Judicial Summit

volunteer_experiences.description:
- Responsible for promoting ACWAY intercultural and interfaith harmony principles in Brazil;
- Represented the Global Youth at the 2016 UN World Interfaith Harmony Conference, in Dubai; and
- Co-drafted the Interfaith Development Goals (IDGs), introduced at the 2018 G20 Interfaith Summit.

- Supervised 48 volunteers on the writing of 8 academic articles (reviewing, editing, giving trainings); 
- Coordinated AMUN Kids, a project that teaches impoverished children about human rights; and
- Planned the content and structure of the 19th AMUN Conference.
